The paper deals with the design of a projection matrix for compressive sensing, which is a topic in both information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of mutual information and entropy measures suggests a signal processing (cs.SP) perspective. The mention of gradients and optimization techniques also points towards multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
